ZH: 志玲一下子看到自己已進入了絕路。
EN: Zhiling suddenly realized she had reached a dead end.

ZH: 他發現自己走出來就是一個絕路。
EN: He found himself at a dead end when he walked out.

ZH: 她感到絕望，因為被困在了一條絕路上。
EN: She felt hopeless as she was trapped on a dead end road.

ZH: 在做出重要的決定之前，我們應該先避免走向絕路。
EN: Before making important decisions, we should avoid walking into a dead end.

ZH: 走到了絕路的盡頭，他意識到了他走錯了地方。
EN: He realized he had taken the wrong path when he reached the end of the dead end road.

ZH: 面對絕路的時候，只能往回走。
EN: When faced with a dead end, the only option is to turn back.

ZH: 絕路是通往成功的唯一途徑。
EN: The dead end is the only way to success.

ZH: 他一路行來，覺得自己似乎一直在走絕路。
EN: He felt like he had been walking on a dead end road the whole way.

ZH: 在重要問題上，不可以選擇走向絕路。
EN: When it comes to important matters, we should not choose the dead end.

ZH: 當你面臨到絕路時，別怕，去尋找轉機。
EN: When you come to a dead end, don't be afraid, look for a turnaround.

ZH: 走上絕路，他頓時感到一陣徬徨。
EN: He felt lost when he found himself on a dead end road.

ZH: 在這條絕路上，他感到了絕望。
EN: He felt despair on this dead end road.

ZH: 退一步三思，不要輕易選擇絕路。
EN: Think twice before choosing the dead end.

ZH: 絕路是暫時的，轉機隨時都會出現。
EN: The dead end is temporary, and opportunities will arise at any time.

ZH: 在最需要的時候，他們走上了絕路。
EN: When they needed it the most, they walked into a dead end.

ZH: 在絕路邊緣，還有希望。
EN: At the edge of the dead end, there is still hope.

ZH: 他不願意承認自己已經走上了絕路。
EN: He was unwilling to admit that he had reached a dead end.

ZH: 走到絕路時，我們還有很多路可以選擇。
EN: When we reach a dead end, we still have many paths to choose from.

ZH: 面對絕路，他毅然決定往前走。
EN: Faced with a dead end, he decisively decided to move forward.

ZH: 對於絕路，最終還是得尋找轉機。
EN: In the face of a dead end, one still needs to find a way out.
